spec: socket_extra160
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "socket_extra159.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.__name__.__eq__('socket') / socket.__module__.__eq__('socket') / socket.__bases__[0].__name__/__module__ / socket.__init__.__qualname__.__eq__('socket.__init__') / socket.connect.__qualname__.__eq__('socket.connect') / socket.__init__/__class__.__name__=='function' / socket.connect/__class__.__name__=='method_descriptor' (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra158.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.AF_INET.__eq__(2) / AF_INET6.__eq__(30) / SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1) / SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__(2) / AF_INET.__class__.__name__.__eq__('AddressFamily') / SOCK_STREAM.__class__.__name__.__eq__('SocketKind') (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra156.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('ModuleSpec') / socket.socket makefile/__setblocking/__settimeout/__getpeername/__getsockname/__setsockopt qualnames and lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra155.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.setdefaulttimeout/__class__.__name__/__module__ / socket.socket.__doc__/__class__.__name__ (table + invariants)."
    - "socket.zspec / early extras — cover socket.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in socket_extra93 through socket_extra159."
    - "Wave 342 theme: socket.socket method qualnames for core networking operations — bind, listen, accept, close qualname strings and lengths; extra159 anchors connect.__qualname__=='socket.connect' (14 chars); this spec anchors bind(11)/listen(13)/accept(13)/close(12) as novel; accept and close are 'function' objects while bind and listen are 'method_descriptor'."
    - "socket.socket.bind.__qualname__ == 'socket.bind'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.listen.__qualname__ == 'socket.listen'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.accept.__qualname__ == 'socket.accept'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.close.__qualname__ == 'socket.close'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.bind.__qualname__.__len__() == 11. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.listen.__qualname__.__len__() == 13. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.accept.__qualname__.__len__() == 13. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.close.__qualname__.__len__() == 12. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: socket.socket.bind.__qualname__ == 'socket.bind' (11 chars = 'socket.'=7 + 'bind'=4). bind() is a method_descriptor inherited from _socket.socket. bind(address) binds the socket to a local address. 'bind' (4 chars) is the shortest method name among the four in this spec. Length ordering: bind(11) < close(12) < listen==accept(13) < connect(14; extra159). The class prefix 'socket.' (7 chars) is the same for all socket.socket methods."
    - "Note: socket.socket.accept.__qualname__ == 'socket.accept' (13 chars = 'socket.'=7 + 'accept'=6). accept() is a pure Python function (not a method_descriptor), overriding the inherited C method to return a socket.socket instance instead of a _socket.socket instance. accept.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: socket.socket.close.__qualname__ == 'socket.close' (12 chars = 'socket.'=7 + 'close'=5). close() is also a pure Python function, overriding the C-level close to perform Python-level cleanup. close.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Both accept and close are pure Python overrides in socket.socket, unlike bind and listen which are inherited method_descriptors from _socket.socket."
    - "Note: socket.socket.listen.__qualname__ == 'socket.listen' (13 chars = 'socket.'=7 + 'listen'=6). listen() is a method_descriptor inherited from _socket.socket (C extension). listen(backlog) marks the socket as a server socket and specifies the number of pending connections the OS should queue. listen.__class__.__name__ == 'method_descriptor'. listen ties accept at 13 chars despite being different types (method_descriptor vs function)."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

